    <note type="biography">
        <p>Scottish horticulturist and pomologist. Gained practical horticultural training with Peter Lawson in Edinburgh and Hugh Ronalds in Brentford, after which he studied in Paris, Belgium, and Germany. Partner in a nursery in Brompton Park, London, 1842–51. Co-editor of the <hi rend="italic">Cottage Gardener</hi> (from 1861, <hi rend="italic">Journal of Horticulture</hi>), 1855–95.</p></note>
